195
00:19:37.967 --> 00:19:43.492
News value is strictly bound by timestamp; tomorrow it's old news, less valuable.

196
00:19:43.492 --> 00:19:47.780
0.4.5 I Read Papers But Couldn't Serve a Dish!

197
00:19:47.780 --> 00:19:55.730
0.4.5.1 Assume first you're a natural resource organizer; below we discuss only which papers make dish-serving easier.

198
00:19:55.730 --> 00:20:03.080
Original spirit is equal before God — Van Gogh's Starry Night and Fermat's Last Theorem both represent human wisdom and dignity

199
00:20:03.080 --> 00:20:11.467
0.4.5.2 For humble, resource-scarce human society/resource allocators, equal distribution cannot be afforded.

200
00:20:11.467 --> 00:20:19.505
Roughly, resources are allocated proportionally to marginal contributions to productivity (per additional 100 PhDs)

201
00:20:19.505 --> 00:20:29.555
0.4.5.3 If the papers you read happen to represent sharp directions of productivity progress, relatively higher probability of obtaining more resources.

202
00:20:29.555 --> 00:20:39.417
In 2504, Terence Tao is one of the world's most successful mathematicians; his annual salary is comparable to 2-3 years of NVIDIA engineer compensation

203
00:20:39.580 --> 00:20:44.655
0.4.5.4 Returning to personal level, life is finite.

204
00:20:44.605 --> 00:20:49.755
An industry with only ten years of history — study seven years and you're an expert.

205
00:20:49.755 --> 00:20:58.105
Conversely, an industry with 50+ years of history requires 30 years of study to become an expert through seniority and relative health alone

206
00:20:58.105 --> 00:21:04.467
0.4.6 Interview with Top Chinese Mathematicians: "What Is Important Mathematics?

207
00:21:04.467 --> 00:21:07.592
How to Tell If You're Suited for Math Research?

208
00:21:07.756 --> 00:21:11.768
R: In the math world, how are resources allocated?

209
00:21:11.718 --> 00:21:14.393
What is important mathematics?

210
00:21:14.393 --> 00:21:22.906
M: Personally I lean toward important mathematics being profound, touching aspects of humanity — akin to why da Vinci is a master artist

211
00:21:22.906 --> 00:21:35.381
R: Taking art as analogy: art has schools (historical inheritance, like discussions you mention), clients (market demand, e.g., architecture), and development (some masters consider certain directions important)

212
00:21:35.381 --> 00:21:37.781
M: Same for math.

213
00:21:37.781 --> 00:21:41.706
One is basic curiosity; one is client demand

214
00:21:41.706 --> 00:21:44.356
R: Two common concerns:

215
00:21:44.356 --> 00:21:49.543
a，Pure math has insufficient total resources, low fault tolerance for talent

216
00:21:49.543 --> 00:21:55.018
b，Given limited resources, informatics has sharp market-demand orientation.

217
00:21:55.018 --> 00:22:02.056
Returning to art analogy: math research should focus on school inheritance / master opinions / client taste

218
00:22:02.056 --> 00:22:03.393
M:

219
00:22:03.393 --> 00:22:05.006
a，Yes.

220
00:22:05.006 --> 00:22:11.143
Develop good taste, do what you consider important, fight for resources — most people are reasonable

221
00:22:11.143 --> 00:22:17.281
b，Productivity advancement direction likely spawns good mathematics too, say quantum computing

222
00:22:17.281 --> 00:22:20.906
R: How to tell if you're suited for math research?

223
00:22:20.906 --> 00:22:22.243
M:

224
00:22:22.243 --> 00:22:25.868
a，Once you have this awareness, you'll figure it out.

225
00:22:25.868 --> 00:22:32.443
One: read mathematician bios/interviews/biographies — see if you admire them, like their lives.

226
00:22:32.443 --> 00:22:39.393
Recommended: Contemporary Mathematical Elite / Contemporary Math Masters; Two: only know by doing

227
00:22:39.393 --> 00:22:43.331
b，Attached: two interviews that deeply influenced me:

228
00:22:43.331 --> 00:22:54.206
https://publications.ias.edu/sites/default/files/interview-ubc-2009-rpl.pdf

229
00:22:54.206 --> 00:23:05.518
https://www.ams.org/journals/notices/201904/rnoti-p494.pdf

230
00:23:05.518 --> 00:23:11.568
0.4.6 From here, our discussion splits into the Non-Elite track and The Elite track

231
00:23:11.568 --> 00:23:15.206
This work is also called RynW4+1.

232
00:23:15.206 --> 00:23:21.018
Chapter 0: How to Truly Live" is hereinafter how0 or "Ch.0", etc.

233
00:23:21.018 --> 00:23:24.181
0.4.6.0 If you:

234
00:23:24.181 --> 00:23:28.856
a，Are willing to serve an original dish to the world — you are one of The Elite

235
00:23:28.856 --> 00:23:32.756
b，Are unwilling — you are (choosing to be) Non-Elite

236
00:23:32.756 --> 00:23:36.618
c，This work contains no value judgment on this point.

237
00:23:36.618 --> 00:23:40.331
Different life choices receive different 5hows routes

238
00:23:40.331 --> 00:23:46.381
d，Core reason for distinction: core drivers differ between tracks, requiring separate discussion.

239
00:23:46.381 --> 00:23:48.243
Specifically:

240
00:23:48.243 --> 00:23:53.831
0.4.6.1 Non-Elites need to master how 1 / how 2 more urgently

241
00:23:53.831 --> 00:23:59.443
0.4.6.2 The Elite need to master how 4 / how 5 more urgently

242
00:23:59.443 --> 00:24:03.468
0.4.6.3 Everyone needs how 3

243
00:24:03.468 --> 00:24:06.206
We begin with the Non-Elite version

244
00:24:06.206 --> 00:24:09.681
How to Truly Live" — Non-Elite Development Track

245
00:24:09.681 --> 00:24:16.418
0.5 I Need Chapter 1: How to Manage Wealth, But Even More I Need the Legendary First Bucket of Gold?

246
00:24:16.418 --> 00:24:25.956
0.5.1 Investment cannot be used for generating first bucket of gold ("investable capital at scale," hereinafter W₀, other aliases follow)

247
00:24:25.956 --> 00:24:31.593
0.5.2 Since ancient times, the official method is providing services.

248
00:24:31.593 --> 00:24:34.268
Providing services" means:

249
00:24:34.268 --> 00:24:41.418
0.5.2.1 You made a contribution to an important person (hereinafter M, other aliases follow)

250
00:24:41.418 --> 00:24:48.931
0.5.2.2 This contribution was so important that M would not replace you upon completion (this is a high standard)

251
00:24:48.931 --> 00:24:54.256
0.5.3 Though your ability may be small, your value to M is large.

252
00:24:54.256 --> 00:24:58.043
M casually tosses you something — now you have W₀

253
00:24:58.043 --> 00:25:04.218
0.5.3.1 Self-starting works too but requires risking loss-of-capital risk

254
00:25:04.218 --> 00:25:09.818
0.5.3.2 If the venture succeeds, you can begin applying 5hows

255
00:25:09.818 --> 00:25:24.293
HK TV drama trope: being M's assistant (arranging travel, booking tickets) for years; before marriage/having kids, M usually gives a code word — since early HK stock manipulation was rampant, sometimes (in dramas) this actually works

256
00:25:24.293 --> 00:25:32.693
0.5.4 Thus the first bucket of gold is not a "market deal" but an "off-market deal" — no universal solution / academic value

257
00:25:32.860 --> 00:25:36.697
0.5.5 M won't pay attention to me.

258
00:25:36.647 --> 00:25:38.310
What to do?

259
00:25:38.310 --> 00:25:43.710
0.5.5.1 You don't need equivalent resources to make M need you

260
00:25:43.710 --> 00:25:48.435
a，Extremely low probability you do — this is a widespread fallacy

261
00:25:48.435 --> 00:25:55.047
b，In fact, meeting M's daily needs has a standard — colloquially, sitting in the "first three rows" of meetings

262
00:25:55.047 --> 00:26:02.122
Specifically: if M has a request and tells A, and A handles it directly — then A is qualified front-row material

263
00:26:02.122 --> 00:26:06.797
Conversely, if B says "ask C to handle this" — B is disqualified.

264
00:26:06.797 --> 00:26:11.547
Long-term, C is better adapted; B handling it wastes efficiency

265
00:26:11.547 --> 00:26:16.460
0.5.5.2 Stable expectations from M suffice

266
00:26:16.460 --> 00:26:20.347
a，M expectation one: insider / one of us

267
00:26:20.347 --> 00:26:27.722
Us" can be broadly defined: childhood friends / alumni / spouse's high school classmates / ex-colleague's spouse all work

268
00:26:27.722 --> 00:26:31.435
Core: has bottom line, doesn't pull surprises

269
00:26:31.435 --> 00:26:40.022
By the way, this is the core social value of HYPSM/Tsinghua-PKU/Fudan-SJTU-ZJU alumni status — no less than e的负一次方

270
00:26:40.022 --> 00:26:43.560
b，M expectation two: upright character

271
00:26:43.560 --> 00:26:49.760
They're busy working, not purely freeloading; what they work on has positive externalities for M

272
00:26:49.760 --> 00:26:57.522
Due to uncommon/invisible nature of M's needs, positive-externality work generally isn't universal technical skill

273
00:26:57.522 --> 00:27:08.060
Cambridge visiting scholar / Singapore family office / Swiss skiing / Dubai ground handling / Japanese medical care / Nobel laureate interview / authentic iron-pot stew…

274
00:27:08.060 --> 00:27:11.772
c，M expectation three: stable context

275
00:27:11.772 --> 00:27:14.585
Meeting regularly builds rapport.

276
00:27:14.585 --> 00:27:21.810
Golf buddies / card buddies / fishing buddies, hiking together / marathon / book club / Maotai tasting…

277
00:27:21.810 --> 00:27:25.085
How to Truly Live" — Elite Development Track

278
00:27:25.085 --> 00:27:28.985
0.6 Essential Characteristics of The Elite

279
00:27:28.985 --> 00:27:34.210
0.6.0 The Elite are responsible only to their own learning curves

280
00:27:34.210 --> 00:27:40.872
Not to anything else (secular achievements, others' evaluation, resource accumulation, social impact)

281
00:27:40.872 --> 00:27:47.572
0.6.0.1 Only learning for yourself ensures every minute spent learning is exactly what you need.

282
00:27:47.572 --> 00:27:52.535
This is why so many foreign university students drop out to start businesses.

283
00:27:52.535 --> 00:27:59.110
To them, studying for a diploma genuinely delays things — delays progress on what they themselves want to learn.

284
00:27:59.110 --> 00:28:09.447
0.6.0.2 If there exists something you do every morning upon waking without anyone prompting — neither physiological nor assigned by others — this is hereinafter "The Passion

285
00:28:09.447 --> 00:28:17.472
0.6.0.3 Finding The Passion, given enough time, makes a significant difference — more important than any resource.

286
00:28:17.472 --> 00:28:26.735
0.6.1 Therefore, as long as your learning curve is steep and The Passion intersects with world demand, your excellence will inevitably be known by the world.

287
00:28:26.735 --> 00:28:33.135
Your excellence cannot be concealed — only you optimizing the world remains, the world cannot optimize you.

288
00:28:33.135 --> 00:28:37.572
Director Jiaozi (of Ne Zha 2) studied medicine originally.

289
00:28:37.572 --> 00:28:41.997
0.6.2 Why doesn't the Elite track discuss W₀?

290
00:28:41.997 --> 00:28:44.485
Because The Elite don't need it

291
00:28:44.485 --> 00:28:52.872
0.6.2.1 The Elite create original contributions; when and how much these are valued depends on world demand emergence and change

292
00:28:52.872 --> 00:29:00.372
a，This is uncertain — in 2504, card game company annual revenue tens of billions, previously unimaginable

293
00:29:00.372 --> 00:29:07.685
0.6.2.2 Later you'll learn investment has a limit return rate GR_m=20%

294
00:29:07.685 --> 00:29:13.185
a，This essentially comes from world demand for money (and the limit of rich people playing it).

295
00:29:13.185 --> 00:29:16.110
The world doesn't need money that badly

296
00:29:16.110 --> 00:29:21.085
0.6.2.3 The Elite answer only to their own learning curves.

297
00:29:21.085 --> 00:29:31.922
After original convex-hull contribution, as long as intersection with world demand (including future demand) is non-empty, monetary value surges — no academic law governs this.

298
00:29:31.922 --> 00:29:38.997
0.6.3 I Made an Original Contribution Intersecting With World Demand — How Do I Know How Big It Can Get?

299
00:29:38.997 --> 00:29:50.197
0.6.3.1 From above: original contributions' size cannot be estimated beforehand; "make it as big as possible" isn't The Elite's initial motive either — realizing The Idea is.

300
00:29:50.197 --> 00:29:53.410
See Ch.4 for related concepts.

301
00:29:53.410 --> 00:30:05.610
0.6.3.2 In practice, judging the scale of an endeavor has a gold standard: if you're position #1 (the driver) and attract n Dream Captains, long-term this endeavor is worth at least RMB nb

302
00:30:05.764 --> 00:30:15.226
a，Because Dream Captains alone can sustain a public company at single-digit billions; they haven't done so because joining your endeavor is more worthwhile (see Ch.4).

303
00:30:15.176 --> 00:30:24.751
In fact, company value increases exponentially with number of Dream Captains — because visions/endeavors capable of gathering more of them are exponentially scarce

304
00:30:24.751 --> 00:30:30.839
b，The converse also holds: if only yourself is Elite in your company, long-term value is zero.

305
00:30:30.839 --> 00:30:37.089
Efficiency-wise, you belong somewhere with more Elites for self-realization, not running your own company

306
00:30:37.252 --> 00:30:41.352
0.6.3.3 Great visions unite hearts

307
00:30:41.302 --> 00:30:45.664
0.7 Before Being Recognized as Elite — What Can You Do?

308
00:30:45.664 --> 00:30:51.039
By definition, Elite is an intrinsic attribute — unrelated to whether others know

309
00:30:51.039 --> 00:30:54.152
0.7.1 How to Read

310
00:30:54.152 --> 00:30:58.964
0.7.1.1 At the highest level, knowledge converges

311
00:30:58.964 --> 00:31:09.677
a，Generally held that studying politics / history / international relations / psychology / philosophy / religion — disciplines reaching human nature — leads to faster awakening

312
00:31:09.677 --> 00:31:17.052
b，Economics / investing / science / engineering / art / design — once mastered, converge similarly

313
00:31:17.052 --> 00:31:27.189
c，Ultimate outcome points toward seeing heaven and earth, seeing oneself, seeing past and present, seeing all beings — finally roughly grasping "Chapter 5: How to Predict the Future

314
00:31:27.189 --> 00:31:34.039
0.7.1.2 Clearly, what matters are non-required readings (required ones you've already read)

315
00:31:34.039 --> 00:31:38.764
a，The world is vast; always allocate e的负一次方 time to non-required readings

316
00:31:38.764 --> 00:31:42.889
With probability 1, The Passion is unknown to you right now

317
00:31:42.889 --> 00:31:46.814
There is zero ambiguity here (if you knew it, you'd know).

318
00:31:46.814 --> 00:31:50.039
Not knowing yet — only reading can reveal it

319
00:31:50.039 --> 00:31:57.052
b，Non-required readings: skim first, speed-read as leisure, conduct feasibility-of-feasibility analysis

320
00:31:57.052 --> 00:32:01.277
Your goal isn't learning — it's determining "is learning this feasible?

321
00:32:01.277 --> 00:32:03.102
does it suit me?

322
00:32:03.102 --> 00:32:05.577
is the author's aesthetic low?

323
00:32:05.577 --> 00:32:11.052
c，Once feasibility established, pick simple spots to dip-read — "learn where you're weak

324
00:32:11.052 --> 00:32:13.827
By now you've invested real cost.

325
00:32:13.827 --> 00:32:16.202
Assess: any gains?

326
00:32:16.202 --> 00:32:18.352
Is this what I'm missing?

327
00:32:18.352 --> 00:32:24.702
Authors write logically; what you need most isn't necessarily presented sequentially — grab whatever helps

328
00:32:24.702 --> 00:32:29.814
d，If all above checks out, go ahead and learn — still pick chapters you need first

329
00:32:29.814 --> 00:32:37.939
The 20% portion of Pareto principle itself follows Pareto: typically 4% of content carries 64% of meaning

330
00:32:37.939 --> 00:32:41.327
0.7.2 How to Make Friends

331
00:32:41.327 --> 00:32:49.889
0.7.2.1 Don't chase celebrities, don't pry into people's lives, don't do things you wouldn't normally do just because you happen to know someone

332
00:32:49.889 --> 00:32:55.177
a，Intersection between people emerges naturally from each person's own endeavors

333
00:32:55.177 --> 00:33:02.977
b，If someone doesn't do related work yet tries to know what others are doing — this pollutes purity of their own pursuits and purity of friendship alike

334
00:33:02.977 --> 00:33:08.439
0.7.2.2 Friends who are upright, forgiving, and widely informed

335
00:33:08.439 --> 00:33:14.402
a，The Elite always desire more friends who are The Elite, even in completely unrelated fields

336
00:33:14.402 --> 00:33:19.114
Science of science exists — vastly different fields converge at the top

337
00:33:19.114 --> 00:33:22.277
b，The Elite inspire and encourage each other

338
00:33:22.277 --> 00:33:27.777
Stuck in Shanghai on a rainy night, late-night snack with an old flame after years out of touch.

339
00:33:27.777 --> 00:33:31.839
Neither of us changed — including weight and his resolve to diet.

340
00:33:31.839 --> 00:33:40.364
We collaborated on many things in college: basically I started he finished, pair programming I talked he coded, weird bugs he stayed up I slept.

341
00:33:40.364 --> 00:33:46.264
His startup on a bizarre venture taught me lots; I shared my brewing bizarre plan for him to critique.

342
00:33:46.264 --> 00:33:50.789
Ended perfectly with three questions about each other's past and future.

343
00:33:50.789 --> 00:33:52.464
Zhang Yiming

344
00:33:52.464 --> 00:33:57.039
This work will quote him multiple times; hereinafter YM or Yiming.

345
00:33:57.039 --> 00:33:59.414
His quotes appear in teal

346
00:33:59.414 --> 00:34:08.389
0.7.2.3 Direct corollary: since university is the flattest social venue, before you find answers to big questions (The Passion?

347
00:34:08.389 --> 00:34:10.277
Who to build with?

348
00:34:10.277 --> 00:34:14.752
To what extent?), why not water two extra years in university?

349
00:34:14.752 --> 00:34:19.977
0.7.3 How to Learn Making Things Happen (see how 4 for details)

350
00:34:19.977 --> 00:34:27.714
0.7.3.0 Selected Works of Mao + Zero to One + How to Be a Commander — basically covers how to do anything

351
00:34:27.714 --> 00:34:35.477
0.7.3.1 "How to Organize" is the first axiom of Mao Selected Works (Chairman Mao hereinafter the Chairman)

352
00:34:35.477 --> 00:34:41.302
a，The Chairman has one merit: among leaders past and present, he likely loves writing most

353
00:34:41.302 --> 00:34:45.952
b，He wishes all masses immediately understood everything he understood

354
00:34:45.952 --> 00:34:53.789
0.7.3.2 He didn't do tech innovation, didn't spend long in middle management — Selected Works lacks these two parts.

355
00:34:53.789 --> 00:34:56.727
Everything else, he covered completely

356
00:34:56.727 --> 00:35:03.227
a，Add "Zero to Hereinafter frequently cited as 《0到1》" and "How to Be a Commander" — you're the secular king

357
00:35:03.388 --> 00:35:08.688
b，Add "Philosophical Investigations" (Wittgenstein) — you're the philosopher king

358
00:35:08.638 --> 00:35:15.225
0.7.3.3 Remaining principles boil down to "concrete analysis of concrete problems

359
00:35:15.225 --> 00:35:24.338
For example, read "Ziyang Telegram" (General Su Yu): "how to write requests" — tried 100 times, works 100 times, counts as a minor principle

360
00:35:24.508 --> 00:35:34.308
0.7.3.4 Textbooks, history, biographies/interviews/quotes of figures, and milestone papers — these four rank equally as best mentors

361
00:35:34.258 --> 00:35:39.558
0.7.3.5 Those planning great deeds should start learning how early

362
00:35:39.558 --> 00:35:45.633
Of course jumping straight into great deeds isn't bad either — saves learning many long-term-useless skills

363
00:35:45.633 --> 00:35:52.858
a，Making things happen requires early practice; sweeping a room vs. sweeping the world share some skills and differ in others

364
00:35:52.858 --> 00:35:58.120
b，If you can outsource the overlapping parts, you really can just learn to sweep the world

365
00:35:58.120 --> 00:36:00.995
The difference set cannot be outsourced.

366
00:36:00.995 --> 00:36:05.395
History proves repeatedly: resource stitching cannot sweep the world

367
00:36:05.395 --> 00:36:11.695
c，If failure 4-6 times precedes success, best to fail 1-2 times during university

368
00:36:11.695 --> 00:36:15.708
YM founded four startups and worked twice before ByteDance

369
00:36:15.708 --> 00:36:20.258
0.7.4 Three Examples of The Elite at Age 20

370
00:36:20.258 --> 00:36:24.058
0.7.4.1 L₁ ~40 years old.

371
00:36:24.058 --> 00:36:29.933
At 20, firmly believed "strive unceasingly / don't live merely for personal wealth freedom

372
00:36:29.933 --> 00:36:34.095
a，Observed real motivation: "make it in the alumni circle

373
00:36:34.095 --> 00:36:38.933
